snippet.textDisplay: I thought I was gonna get super triggered but hey it's you we're talking about, you weren't going to say anything weird. I perfectly understand, reading should be done when you feel like it and some people don't like to read that often, but it doesn't mean they hate reading, come on sometimes I read 4 books a week and sometimes I spend 2 months without even looking at one, it depends, but when something is forced there's really no helping it. My school I think did this the right way, the teacher let us choose our book, gave us some reasonable questions and a good amount of time, but if I was forced to read animal farm and completely decipher it in record time I would've told Orwell to piss off with 1984, which is one of my favorite books of all time but I wouldn't have even read it. To summarize, just read what you like and as much as you desire, forced everything is bad

I’ve never read the book but my older brother did and was talking about it with my mom when I came downstairs. They talked about this guy named Lenny or something and apparently he died. Now, normally you don’t remember stuff like this, but seeing it in the video makes me remember whenever it’s brought up. You can’t just try to forget it or you’ll remember so I tried naturally forgetting it, but I can’t. It’ll just randomly pop up in my head like “oh yeah I hope I don’t have to read Animal Farm later, oh yeah, Lenny dies in the book”. You know, normal human brain stuff. Goddamnit Lenny I hope you weren’t too important because I’ll be in my brothers grade eventually.

snippet.textDisplay: I love reading very much and just saying, reading isn't necessarily limited to books. This may sound strange to those who believe that it's all just inappropriate, but fanfiction is actually really enjoyable. Not the dirty or badly written ones but the ones with rich stories and original ideas that add onto canon characters while not taking away from who they are in the process. Although I do enjoy books, it's more fun to read fanfic because of the familiarity of the characters, the bonding between people who share the same interest and especially (in some cases) the humor. I dont think you're gonna find vine or meme references in a book anytime soon. So just putting it out there to those who dont know, fanfic is actually pretty neat and I probably sound really dumb writing all of this but ITS IMPORTANT TO ME O K A Y?? (Hope you guys have a nice day lol)

snippet.textDisplay: I’ve never liked reading. I’m dyslexic, it’s hard for me, my parents and schools made me read. I do have a low reading level, but I do try to read from time to time. I now listen to the audiobooks while having a physical book in my hand and following along. I don’t want to stare at a tv all day, so I try and read for like 40 minutes a day ( that’s about as long as it takes me to get through a hard Potter order of the Phoenix chapter). Sometimes I do more like I did yesterday. I probably did closer to 2 hours, reading about 40 minutes of each book that I’ve been reading yesterday.
